column5: New tires for my ATV, trailer for ATV and snowmobile (tired of loading both into truck) New silverado, a really big Lund with a huge Honda on it and a nice kicker and ALL the doodads and nicknacs and a month of great Canadian fishing away from my wife- er- I mean work! Anybody got an extra hundred grand they don't need?

12 magnum bulldawgs 11 super shad raps 10 trophy muskies 9 polar tipups 8 horsepower kicker 7 yellow jigs 6 spinning reels 5 FLY IN TTTTRRRIIIPPPSSS!! 4 rainbow trout 3 pricey rods 2 downriggers AND A WALLEYE IN A PEAR TREE ! :D

I would like for my brother to be able to finish colege. He is 19 years old and does not have enogh money to go to colege anymore. He has to work to pay his bills. I would like for th world to stop fighting. I dont like it when people kil each other on the tv at night. I would like for my mom to be a happy lady, and stop cryingn at night. I would like for the kidz at school to be nice to me. I would like for my dad to come back home and love my mom and me. Sorry for the long list Santa. Please tend to those who are mor neady than me and my family Jacob Fesler

Hello Santa. I'd like to get you to try and bring back some of the values of years gone by. The perfect gift thing is getting a bit tired for me. We had people as a youngster who came to the house for dinner at Christmas and all they brought was a firm handshake and good stories. They were just getting by. Oh and Santa please keep our young men and woman safe who are in harms way. I know I'm being very greedy now Santa and I know this is a stretch but could you talk to the Big Guy and get the Toronto Mapleleafs to win the Stanley Cup and bring it home to Canada where it belongs .....away from those Crawfish eating southerners.

My neighbor plays Santa Claus at various events. He told me that he was at an office party last year and the employees had their children there. He went on to tell me that a little girl about 3 or 4 years old old climbed up on his lap and told Santa her name was Allysa. When Santa asked her what she wanted for xmas her reply was short and to the point "I want my Daddy back from Iraq, I love my Daddy"

In the second week of June, I had a rod bender on Lac Seul. It was a big one, but did not feel like a pike. I thought I finally had my 30"++ walleye on, and was calling for the camera.......and then it spit the hook before I could see it. *&$%(&$%$#&&(%!!!!!!!! I want Santa to tell me it was just decent sized Pike so I can stop kicking myself!!!!!!!
